Protect Sensitive Data by Masking Customer Phone Numbers

Keep customer phone numbers confidential by enabling phone number masking from the Contact Center Setup page. With this feature enabled, all phone numbers appear in Omni-Channel views, call recordings, and transcripts as “Masked Number.” The only phone numbers that aren’t masked are ones used in agent-to-agent calls managed by partner telephony providers.

Where: This change applies to Lightning Experience in Enterprise and Unlimited editions. Available in Salesforce orgs with these telephony models.
